  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../local-officials-pressured-turn-around-poor-showing-energy-intensity-numbers">Local Officials Pressured to Turn Around Poor Showing in Energy Intensity Numbers</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Deborah Seligsohn</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">May 07, 2010</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>This week China held its second high-level discussion in two weeks on implementing its energy intensity target  at the same time as disappointing first quarter numbers appeared showing that energy intensity has risen by 3.2% in the first quarter of 2010.   Premier Wen Jiabao told provincial officials to use <a href="http://www.upi.com/Science_News/Resource-Wars/2010/05/06/China-iron-hand-to-reach-energy-targets/UPI-22221273162633/">“an iron hand”</a> in implementing energy intensity targets.  This comes in the wake of last weeks’ announcement of <a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../china-major-push-meet-20-energy-intensity-target">eight new policies</a> to enhance implementation of the 20% energy intensity target.</p></div>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-view-node">
                <span class="field-content"><div class="readmore"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../local-officials-pressured-turn-around-poor-showing-energy-intensity-numbers">Read More</a></div></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-tid">
          <label class="views-label-tid">
        Issue Areas:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/energy-efficiency">Energy Efficiency</a>, <a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/industry">Industry</a>, <a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/measurement-and-compliance">Measurement and Compliance</a>, <a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../category/issue-areas/policy-and-governance">Policy and Governance</a></span>
  </div>
  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-9 views-row-odd">
      
  <div class="views-field-field-image-fid">
                <span class="field-content"><img src="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../files/chinainfo/imagecache/news-image/power_lines_5-10-10.jpg" alt="" title="" width="90" height="120" class="imagecache imagecache-news-image imagecache-default imagecache-news-image_default"/></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-title">
                <span class="field-content"><a href="../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../../china-major-push-meet-20-energy-intensity-target">China in Major Push to Meet 20% Energy Intensity Target</a></span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-field-author-value">
          <label class="views-label-field-author-value">
        Posted by:
      </label>
                <span class="field-content">Deborah Seligsohn</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-created">
                <span class="field-content">April 30, 2010</span>
  </div>
  
  <div class="views-field-teaser">
                <div class="field-content"><p>China’s State Council met Wednesday, April 28, and adopted eight new measures to try to spur the country in a final push to meet its 20% energy intensity reduction target during the 5 years from 2006 to the end of 2010.  While the State Council’s decision has been reported in the international media, we found <a href="http://money.hexun.com/2010-04-29/123571006.html">the specific measures</a> only in the Chinese press, which we summarize:</p></div>
  </div>
  
